The paper deals with the concept of equilibrium in exchange economies, which is a central topic in game theory (cs.GT) and algorithmic game theory (cs.AI). The paper also involves the study of allocation algorithms (cs.DS) and the analysis of their performance in terms of stability and optimality. The concept of local equilibrium is related to the notion of convergence in learning algorithms, which is a topic in machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper discusses the limitations of Walrasian equilibria, which is a classical topic in economics and mechanism design (cs.EC).
